ember 2 (NR2F2) (Mendoza-Villarroel et al. 2014), is a nuclear receptor involved in various metabolic systems including lipid regulation and steroid synthesis (Qin et al. 2008; van den Driesche et al. 2012; Ashraf et al. 2018). &nbsp; COUP-TFII has been shown to interact with Retinoid X Receptor (RXR) by forming heterodimers and binding to Glucocorticoid Receptor (GR) (Ashraf et al. 2018).&nbsp;", "timestamp": "Fri May 15 21:35:06 +0000 2026"}